<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">&gt; What explains the slowdown in IANA timezone database updates?<p>My guess is that with the increasing dependency on digital systems for our lives the edge-cases where these rules aren&#x27;t properly updated cause increased amounts of pain &quot;for no good reason&quot;.<p>In Brazil we recently changed our DST rules, it was around 2017&#x2F;2018. It caused a lot of confusion. I was working with a system where these changes were really important, so I was aware of this change ahead of time. But there are a lot of systems running without too much human intervention, and they are mostly forgotten until someone notices a problem.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371743&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44370426%2344371743" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
